  "body": "**_Type_**: Bug\n**_Summary_**: When message is sent while blue progress bar in progress it very often ends up with the `Not connected. Tap for options` status. But in fact, the message reached mailserver fine since it can be received later from offline inbox\n\nIt's follow up issue to whisper-level mailserver message reliability improvement made in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/7243 \nPlease see video between Desktop (sender) and iOS (receiver) here: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1TG23DfjxwdBDnY06B-AjRIKACVRS0o5Z/view showing the issue.\n\nIn a case of Fetching messages which are in progress the message statuses about successfully reaching mailsever fails to be received back by the message sender and so that's why `Not connected. Tap for options`. From the offered options `Resend` / `Delete` message can be deleted but it will be deleted only for message sender. \n\n#### Expected behavior\nMessage is marked as 'Sent' if it was sent when user connected to mailsever\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\"Not connected. Tap for options\" status for messages sent while fetching from mailserver in progress\n![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/53232741-75261300-3694-11e9-96d9-80fd25d4b770.png)\n\n### Reproduction\n\n\n* Open Status\n* Create new account (do not wait until blue progress bar disappears) and\n* Join public chat (e.g. `#whisperconfirmtest`)\n* Send text message\n\n### Solution\n### Additional Information\n\n\n* Status version: Develop\n* Operating System: Android, iOS, Desktop OSs\n\n#### Logs\n[Status.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2893185/Status.log)\n from Desktop build for video session above:\n\n",
